+
+# Vellum as GitHub Governance Bus
+
+## The Problem
+
+Vellum is a ledger and GitHub is a toolchain. They don't talk to each other. Copilot reviews, Dependabot PRs, DeepSeek Five Rods reviews, CI checks, Linear syncs, deploys — each one fires in GitHub, produces a result, and Vellum knows nothing about it. The governance is theatre because the tools that enforce it don't report through the governance surface.
+
+## The Idea
+
+Every GitHub automation pushes a Vellum entry. Vellum knows the expected sequence from prior steps. When a step is missing or late, Vellum flags it. The hash chain becomes the audit trail for the entire development lifecycle, not just agent conversations.
+
+## Two-Stage Filtering Architecture
+
+This design implements the two-stage filtering architecture from first principles:
+
+```
+Input Filters (Rejection on the way in)
+    ├── HMAC-SHA256 webhook signature validation
+    ├── Vellum entry validation (hash chain, attribution, tiers)
+    ├── Five Rods enforcement on PRs (auto-review)
+    ├── Epistemic tier enforcement (Python rejects silent promotion)
+    └── Agent routing rules (park if no clear rule)
+    ↓
+Clean Data in the System
+    ↓
+Design / Architecture
+    ↓
+Third-Party Structural Review (Perplexity — indicator node)
+    ↓
+Implementation
+    ↓
+Output Filters (Validation on the way out)
+    ├── Pattern recognition (agents)
+    ├── Statistical validation (architect)
+    ├── Human decision-making (Ewan)
+    ├── Legal layer (third-party solicitor, when clients exist)
+    └── Protected testing (feature branches, staging)
+    ↓
+Operational Decision
+```
+
+## What Already Exists
+
+### GitHub Side
+
+Five GitHub Actions workflows on `clean-build` (representative of the org pattern):
+
+| Workflow | Trigger | What it does | Current output |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| `pr-validation.yml` | PR opened/sync | Linear ticket check, branch naming, markdown lint, YAML frontmatter, Python lint (ruff) | GitHub check status |
+| `auto-review-merge.yml` | PR opened/sync | DeepSeek Five Rods review, auto-merge on pass | PR comment + merge |
+| `linear-sync.yml` | PR opened/merged/closed | Posts PR link to Linear ticket, moves to "In Review" | Linear comment |
+| `process-health-weekly.yml` | scheduled | Process health metrics | *(unknown — not read)* |
+| `cove-orchestrator-tests.yml` | PR | *(legacy — not read)* | test results |
+
+Plus GitHub-native tools:
+- **Copilot** code review (via `.github/copilot-review-instructions.md`)
+- **Dependabot** (weekly Monday 09:00 UTC, github-actions ecosystem)
+- **CODEOWNERS** (requires `@ewanbramley` for `00_authority/**`, `01_truth/**`)
+
+### Vellum Side
+
+- **Hash-chained entries** — every entry: author, timestamp, content, prev_hash, entry_hash, epistemic_tier, metadata envelope
+- **Entry types** — `agent_write`, `decision`, `health_check`, `metric`, `telemetry`, etc.
+- **Message bus** — asyncio pub/sub, SSE streaming to connected agents
+- **Agent roster** — 8 agents registered with inboxes
+- **Sheets** — main conversation, per-agent inboxes, estate-status telemetry
+- **Dashboard** — Fleet grid at `/comms/grid`
+
+## Architecture: Five Components
+
+### 1. GitHub Webhook Receiver
+
+New Vellum endpoint: `POST /api/v1/hooks/github`
+
+Receives GitHub webhook events, validates HMAC-SHA256 signature, writes a Vellum entry to a dedicated `github-events` sheet.
+
+```python
+GITHUB_ENTRY_TYPES = frozenset({
+    "github_pr_created",
+    "github_pr_merged",
+    "github_pr_closed",
+    "github_ci_check",
+    "github_review_posted",
+    "github_dependabot_pr",
+    "github_linear_synced",
+    "github_push",
+})
+```
+
+Each entry carries:
+
+```json
+{
+  "entry_type": "github_ci_check",
+  "author": "github-actions",
+  "content": "PR #130 — pr-validation/linear-ticket: PASS",
+  "epistemic_tier": "MEASURED",
+  "metadata": {
+    "source": "github_webhook",
+    "repo": "Amplified-Partners/clean-build",
+    "pr_number": 130,
+    "check_name": "Linear ticket reference",
+    "check_status": "success",
+    "actor": "github-actions[bot]",
+    "process_id": "pr-130-clean-build"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+The `process_id` links all entries for one PR lifecycle.
+
+### 2. Process Templates (Expected Sequences)
+
+Define what should happen after each step. Stored as JSON config in Vellum.
+
+Process templates are treated as authority files — changes require Five Rods review via the same DeepSeek workflow that reviews code changes. (Addition from Perplexity structural review.)
+
+```json
+{
+  "template_id": "pr_lifecycle_clean_build",
+  "repo": "Amplified-Partners/clean-build",
+  "steps": [
+    {
+      "id": "pr_created",
+      "entry_type": "github_pr_created",
+      "expected_after": null,
+      "timeout_minutes": null
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "structural_review",
+      "entry_type": "structural_review",
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": null,
+      "required_if": "new_shape == true",
+      "note": "Third-party structural review for new patterns/shapes"
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "linear_sync",
+      "entry_type": "github_linear_synced",
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 5,
+      "skip_if": "actor == dependabot[bot]"
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "branch_check",
+      "entry_type": "github_ci_check",
+      "filter": {"check_name": "Branch name convention"},
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 10
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "ticket_check",
+      "entry_type": "github_ci_check",
+      "filter": {"check_name": "Linear ticket reference"},
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 10,
+      "skip_if": "actor == dependabot[bot]"
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "markdown_lint",
+      "entry_type": "github_ci_check",
+      "filter": {"check_name": "Markdown validation"},
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 10
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "python_lint",
+      "entry_type": "github_ci_check",
+      "filter": {"check_name": "Python lint (ruff)"},
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 10
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "copilot_review",
+      "entry_type": "github_review_posted",
+      "filter": {"actor": "copilot[bot]"},
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 30
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "deepseek_review",
+      "entry_type": "github_review_posted",
+      "filter": {"actor": "github-actions"},
+      "expected_after": "pr_created",
+      "timeout_minutes": 30
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "merge_or_close",
+      "entry_type": ["github_pr_merged", "github_pr_closed"],
+      "expected_after": ["deepseek_review", "copilot_review"],
+      "timeout_minutes": null
+    },
+    {
+      "id": "linear_sync_close",
+      "entry_type": "github_linear_synced",
+      "filter": {"action": "closed"},
+      "expected_after": "merge_or_close",
+      "timeout_minutes": 5
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+Vellum already has the knowledge of the previous step because the template encodes the dependency graph. When `pr_created` arrives, Vellum immediately knows: "I expect `linear_sync` within 5 minutes, `branch_check` within 10 minutes, `deepseek_review` within 30 minutes..."
+
+### 3. Process Tracker (Gap Detector)
+
+A background coroutine that runs inside Vellum:
+
+```python
+class ProcessTracker:
+    """Tracks active process instances against templates.
+
+    When a GitHub event arrives:
+    1. Find or create the process instance for this PR
+    2. Mark the corresponding step as completed
+    3. Check what steps are now expected (unlocked by this completion)
+    4. Schedule timeout alerts for each expected step
+
+    When a timeout fires:
+    1. Check if the step arrived since scheduling
+    2. If not: post a Vellum entry of type 'process_gap'
+    3. Check if the gap has a known precondition failure (park if so)
+    4. Notify via SSE bus (all connected agents see the gap)
+    5. Dashboard shows the gap in red
+    """
+```
+
+Gap entries:
+
+```json
+{
+  "entry_type": "metric",
+  "author": "vellum-process-tracker",
+  "content": "GAP: PR #130 clean-build — expected 'deepseek_review' within 30min of 'pr_created', not received.",
+  "epistemic_tier": "MEASURED",
+  "metadata": {
+    "process_id": "pr-130-clean-build",
+    "missing_step": "deepseek_review",
+    "expected_after": "pr_created",
+    "timeout_minutes": 30,
+    "gap_type": "timeout"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+#### Gap Parking (Addition from Perplexity structural review)
+
+When a gap is detected and the cause is a known precondition failure (e.g. "DeepSeek API is down"), the gap is parked rather than repeatedly alerting:
+
+```json
+{
+  "entry_type": "process_gap_parked",
+  "author": "vellum-process-tracker",
+  "content": "PARKED: PR #130 deepseek_review gap — precondition unmet: DeepSeek API down.",
+  "epistemic_tier": "MEASURED",
+  "metadata": {
+    "process_id": "pr-130-clean-build",
+    "parked_step": "deepseek_review",
+    "precondition": "deepseek_api_healthy",
+    "unpark_when": "health_check:deepseek passes"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### 4. Reconciliation Job (Addition from Perplexity structural review)
+
+GitHub webhooks are best-effort delivery. Missed webhooks = missed entries = broken audit trails. Belt-and-braces (Option C) reduces but doesn't eliminate this risk.
+
+Hourly scheduled job:
+
+```python
+async def reconcile_github_to_vellum():
+    """Query GitHub API for recent PR activity, compare to Vellum entries,
+    flag discrepancies. This catches missed webhooks."""
+    github_prs = await github_api.get_recent_prs(hours=1)
+    vellum_entries = await store.get_recent_entries(hours=1, sheet="github-events")
+    discrepancies = find_discrepancies(github_prs, vellum_entries)
+    if discrepancies:
+        for d in discrepancies:
+            await post_reconciliation_entry(d)
+```
+
+Reconciliation entries are `MEASURED` (deterministic comparison of two data sources).
+
+### 5. Governance Export (Addition from Perplexity structural review)
+
+Nightly export of governance receipts from Vellum to GitHub for pattern recognition by removed nodes (Perplexity):
+
+```
+vellum-record/
+├── bundles/
+│   └── {bundle_id}.json          # Full ExportBundle
+├── entries/
+│   └── {entry_id}.json           # Individual entries with critical fields
+├── faults/
+│   └── {fault_id}.json           # Fault records
+└── index.json                    # Global index
+```
+
+Critical fields for pattern recognition (from Perplexity data requirements):
+
+```json
+{
+  "entry_id": "uuid",
+  "content": "PR #130 — deepseek_review: APPROVED",
+  "epistemic_tier": "STRUCTURED",
+  "prev_tier": "INTUITED",
+  "premises": ["entry-id-1"],
+  "contradicts": [],
+  "depends_on": ["decision-id-3"],
+  "author": "github-actions",
+  "timestamp": "2026-05-24T14:23:00Z"
+}
+```
+
+This enables Perplexity to detect: tier laundering paths, dependency bottlenecks, contradiction clusters, cross-agent consistency, decision drift from documentation.
+
+## Integration Points
+
+### Option A: GitHub Actions Step (Simple)
+
+Add a final step to each workflow that POSTs to Vellum:
+
+```yaml
+- name: Report to Vellum
+  if: always()
+  env:
+    VELLUM_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.VELLUM_WEBHOOK_TOKEN }}
+  run: |
+    curl -s -X POST http://135.181.161.131:8400/api/v1/hooks/receipt \
+      -H "Authorization: Bearer $VELLUM_TOKEN" \
+      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+      -d '{
+        "step": "deepseek_review",
+        "repo": "${{ github.repository }}",
+        "pr_number": ${{ github.event.pull_request.number }},
+        "result": "${{ job.status }}",
+        "actor": "github-actions"
+      }'
+```
+
+Pro: Zero infrastructure. One curl per workflow. Each tool reports itself.
+Con: Requires adding a step to every workflow. If the step fails, no receipt.
+
+### Option B: GitHub Webhook (Comprehensive)
+
+Configure org-level webhook pointing at Vellum. GitHub pushes ALL events. Vellum filters and records.
+
+Pro: Catches everything — even events with no workflow (direct pushes, manual reviews, Copilot reviews). One config, all repos.
+Con: Requires Vellum to be reachable from GitHub. Higher event volume — need filtering.
+
+### Option C: Both (Belt and Braces) — SELECTED
+
+Webhook catches the events automatically. Workflow steps add richer data (e.g., the actual review verdict, the specific check results). Vellum deduplicates by `process_id` + `step_id`. Reconciliation job catches anything both miss.
+
+OPINION 85%. The webhook is the safety net, the workflow steps are the rich signal, the reconciliation job is the dead man's switch.
+
+## Epistemic Tier of Each Tool
+
+| Tool | Event | Vellum Entry | Epistemic Tier |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| GitHub (webhook) | PR opened | `github_pr_created` | MEASURED |
+| PR Validation — branch check | CI check passed/failed | `github_ci_check` | MEASURED |
+| PR Validation — ticket check | CI check passed/failed | `github_ci_check` | MEASURED |
+| PR Validation — markdown lint | CI check passed/failed | `github_ci_check` | MEASURED |
+| PR Validation — python lint | CI check passed/failed | `github_ci_check` | MEASURED |
+| DeepSeek Five Rods review | Review posted | `github_review_posted` | **STRUCTURED** |
+| Copilot code review | Review posted | `github_review_posted` | **STRUCTURED** |
+| Perplexity structural review | Indicator opinion | `structural_review` | **STRUCTURED** |
+| Linear Sync | Ticket updated | `github_linear_synced` | MEASURED |
+| Dependabot | Dependency PR opened | `github_dependabot_pr` | MEASURED |
+| CODEOWNERS | Review required/approved | `github_review_posted` | MEASURED |
+| GitHub (webhook) | PR merged/closed | `github_pr_merged`/`closed` | MEASURED |
+| Reconciliation job | Discrepancy found | `reconciliation_discrepancy` | MEASURED |
+
+DeepSeek, Copilot, and Perplexity reviews are STRUCTURED, not MEASURED — they are AI opinions, not deterministic checks. The min-rule applies.
+
+## Dashboard: Process View
+
+New panel on the Fleet grid or a dedicated `/comms/processes` view:
+
+```
+┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│ PR #130 — clean-build — "ops audit framework"       │
+│ Status: IN PROGRESS                                  │
+│                                                       │
+│ ✓ pr_created         (devon, 14:23)                  │
+│ ✓ structural_review  (perplexity, 14:40)             │
+│ ✓ linear_sync        (github-actions, 14:23)         │
+│ ✓ branch_check       (github-actions, 14:25)         │
+│ ✓ ticket_check       (github-actions, 14:25)         │
+│ ✓ markdown_lint      (github-actions, 14:26)         │
+│ ○ python_lint        (running... 2min)               │
+│ ○ copilot_review     (expected within 30min)         │
+│ ○ deepseek_review    (expected within 30min)         │
+│ · merge_or_close     (blocked on reviews)            │
+│ · linear_sync_close  (blocked on merge)              │
+└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+
+┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+│ PR #131 — vellum — "webhook receiver"                │
+│ Status: GAP DETECTED                                 │
+│                                                       │
+│ ✓ pr_created         (devon, 13:01)                  │
+│ ✓ linear_sync        (github-actions, 13:01)         │
+│ ✗ deepseek_review    OVERDUE (expected by 13:31)     │
+│ ✓ copilot_review     (copilot, 13:15)                │
+│ · merge_or_close     (blocked: deepseek_review)      │
+└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+## Noise Reduction (Addition from Perplexity structural review)
+
+A busy week with 20 PRs across 7 repos = hundreds of Vellum entries. Without filtering, the dashboard becomes a firehose.
+
+Noise reduction layer before the dashboard:
+- Aggregate by `process_id` — show one row per PR, not one row per event
+- Show only active PRs (last event within 24h)
+- Collapse CI checks into a single "CI status" indicator unless a check failed
+- Suppress Dependabot PRs unless they fail
+- GAP entries always surface regardless of filters
+
+## Dead Man's Switch (Addition from Perplexity structural review)
+
+If Beast goes down, no governance receipts arrive. GitHub Actions still run — they just don't report to Vellum.
+
+If Vellum is unreachable for > 30 minutes:
+1. Workflow receipt steps fail silently (`if: always()` prevents blocking the workflow)
+2. Reconciliation job cannot run (it's on Beast too)
+3. Gap detector flags everything as missing (false positives)
+
+Mitigation: periodic external health check (from GitHub Actions scheduled workflow) that pings Vellum and posts to a Slack/WhatsApp channel if unreachable. This is the dead man's switch — separate from Beast, watches Beast.
+
+## Scaling Across Repos
+
+Process templates are per-repo (different repos have different CI). The webhook receiver is org-wide. One Vellum instance serves all repos.
+
+Current repos with GitHub Actions:
+- **clean-build** — 5 workflows (full validation + Five Rods + Linear sync)
+- **marketing-engine** — auto-review + dependabot
+- **crm** — auto-review + dependabot
+- **vellum** — auto-review + dependabot
+- **amplified-knowledge-mcp** — dependabot
+- All other active repos — at minimum dependabot
+
+Each repo gets its own process template. Vellum tracks them all on one sheet.
+
+## Implementation Plan
+
+### Phase 1: Webhook Receiver (1 session)
+- Add `POST /api/v1/hooks/github` endpoint to Vellum
+- HMAC-SHA256 signature validation
+- Map GitHub events to Vellum entry types
+- Write entries to `github-events` sheet
+- Configure org-level webhook on GitHub
+
+### Phase 2: Workflow Receipts (1 session)
+- Add Vellum receipt step to `auto-review-merge.yml`
+- Add Vellum receipt step to `pr-validation.yml`
+- Add Vellum receipt step to `linear-sync.yml`
+- Generate and store `VELLUM_WEBHOOK_TOKEN` as org secret
+- Test end-to-end: open PR → see entries appear on Vellum
+
+### Phase 3: Process Templates + Tracker (1-2 sessions)
+- Build process template JSON schema
+- Create templates for `clean-build` and `vellum` repos
+- Build `ProcessTracker` background coroutine
+- Gap detection with SSE alerts
+- Gap parking for known precondition failures
+- Dashboard panel for active processes
+
+### Phase 4: Multi-Repo + Reconciliation + Export (1 session)
+- Roll out to remaining active repos
+- Build hourly reconciliation job
+- Build nightly governance export to `vellum-record/`
+- Add alert routing (gaps → agent inboxes, Ewan's inbox)
+- Weekly process health summary
+- Dead man's switch (external health check workflow)
+
+## Risks (Assessed by Perplexity, 2026-05-24)
+
+| Risk | Assessment | Mitigation |
+|---|---|---|
+| Single point of failure (Beast) | Real. If Beast is down, no receipts. Local queuing is incomplete without flush. | Dead man's switch: external health check, separate from Beast. |
+| Webhook reliability | GitHub webhooks are best-effort. Missed webhooks = broken audit trails. | Belt-and-braces (Option C) + hourly reconciliation job. |
+| Noise overwhelms signal | 20 PRs × 7 repos = hundreds of entries. Dashboard becomes firehose. | Noise reduction layer: aggregate by process_id, collapse CI, suppress Dependabot. |
+| Complexity budget | New subsystem before agents are connected. Risk of infrastructure for infrastructure's sake. | Counter: this IS the governance that was missing. But validate with a clear use case: "What process failure does this prevent?" |
+| Secret management | Org-level VELLUM_WEBHOOK_TOKEN + webhook secret need provisioning and rotation. | Add to existing secrets rotation process. |
+| Epistemic tier of reviews | DeepSeek/Copilot are STRUCTURED, not MEASURED. Treating as equivalent to CI would be status laundering. | Process template marks review steps as STRUCTURED. Min-rule enforced. |
+
+## The Core Principle
+
+Vellum already enforces honesty on data (hash chain, min-rule, append-only). This extends it to process — every step in the development lifecycle has a receipt, the receipts chain together, and gaps are visible. The third-party structural review extends it further — every design is checked against the structure before it becomes code.
+
+The existing GitHub workflows are the tools. Vellum is the witness. The process template is the expectation. The gap detector is the accountability. The structural review is the filter between design and implementation. The reconciliation job is the safety net. The export is the learning path.
+
+Don't try to fix inherent flaws. Design nets that catch them at the boundary before they propagate to the next stage.
+
